%N A396270 Decimal expansion of the aspect ratio of a rectangle with the property that a straight line drawn through a uniformly random point on its perimeter, with direction chosen uniformly at random, intersects each of the three sides on which the point does not lie with an equal probability.
%C A396270 The larger of the two real solutions of the equation (2*x*arctan(x) + 2*arccot(x) - x*log(x) - (x+1)*log(x^2+1))/(x+1) = Pi/3. The other solution is the reciprocal of this constant, 0.549078357517... .
%e A396270 1.821233684245171515871469793874733272816961833410842...
%t A396270 RealDigits[r /. FindRoot[(2*r*ArcTan[r] + 2*ArcCot[r] + 2*r*Log[r] - (r+1)*Log[r^2+1])/(r+1) == Pi/3, {r, 2}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A396270 (PARI) solve(r = 1, 2, (2*r*atan(r) + 2*atan(1/r) + 2*r*log(r) - (r+1)*log(r^2+1))/(r+1) - Pi/3)
%Y A396270 Cf. A156649, A284983, A300284, A395597, A395598, A396271.
